      "purposeInStoryline": "In Lesson 1 students observed that bubbles emerged from specific spots on submerged sukuma wiki leaves, not uniformly across the entire surface. Lesson 2 resolves the first layer of that mystery: those spots are stomata (and other specialised structures). By naming, locating, and modelling these sites students gather the anatomical evidence needed to later explain why bubbles appear where they do, why temperature matters, and — ultimately — how plant respiration works at the cellular level.",
